<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="865" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="53.[160,1155,282,340]" pageId="53" pageNumber="865">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,292,282,306]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="865">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after ‘Kubera’, the king of the Yakshas (benevolent nature spirits), in Hindu mythology. The name is treated as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
